>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Combat Stability and Natural Durability AA</span><hr size=1> ND takes into effect stam and HP on items worn.  A 125/125 item becomes a 137/125 item.<br>
<br>
It is VERY possible and likely that wizards will pop the 3k unbuffed mark soon.  Click on my profile below if you don't believe me.  I can count at least 4 items I have that are in line for 50-90hp upgrades.  Add onto that ND and tada!!!  3000hp unbuffed.<br>
<br>
If you don't believe this, check out frozboz's profile.  He's about 2 months ahead of me.  3k unbuffed is only a matter of time for him to snag his ND.  If I'm not 3k+ by PoP, I'll be quite disapointed.  So will any number of wizards across many servers.<br>
<br>
And really... we cant consider the argument that this is only the high end casters... because its all relative.  If the average wizard gets less hp from ND than me, so what?  The average warrior gets less than the VT warrior does.  Gotta compare like and like.<br>
<br>
At the end of the day I -LOVE- ND.  I was always a HP freak, but that doesn't mean I think it's good for the game.  And those are two VERY different things.   <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=315013">Shard Elay</a>
